---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Home
description: Katie Anderson — UX designer and researcher.
---

{# ============================================================
   Hero
   ============================================================ #}
<section id="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero__content">
      <h1 class="hero__tagline" id="hero-heading">
        I take the messy, undefined stuff &mdash; <em>research, design, and enough code to make it real.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero__sub">Katie Anderson &mdash; UX Designer &amp; Researcher &mdash; Open to work</p>
    </div>

    {# First case study card lives in the hero #}
    <a class="card hero__card" href="{{ '/case-studies/body-diagram/' | url }}">
      <div class="card__image--placeholder" aria-hidden="true">[ Project thumbnail ]</div>
      <div class="card__body">
        <p class="card__context">Phreesia &mdash; B2B2C</p>
        <h2 class="card__title">The body diagram that locked people out</h2>
        <p class="card__desc">A legacy questionnaire had never worked for keyboard or screen reader users. Making it accessible meant rethinking what "equivalent experience" actually means.</p>
      </div>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================================
   Case Studies
   ============================================================ #}
<section id="case-studies" class="section" aria-labelledby="case-studies-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section__header">
      <h2 class="section__title" id="case-studies-heading">Work</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="case-studies__grid">

      <a class="card" href="{{ '/case-studies/marketing-opt-in-form/' | url }}">
        <div class="card__image--placeholder" aria-hidden="true">[ Project thumbnail ]</div>
        <div class="card__body">
          <p class="card__context">AstraZeneca &mdash; iOS/Android</p>
          <h3 class="card__title">When patients stop logging</h3>
          <p class="card__desc">Scaling a mobile health app to four chronic conditions, while pushing back on leadership's plan to add a fifth before the core behavior was validated.</p>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a class="card" href="{{ '/case-studies/internal-accessibility-site/' | url }}">
        <div class="card__image--placeholder" aria-hidden="true">[ Project thumbnail ]</div>
        <div class="card__body">
          <p class="card__context">Fidelity Investments &mdash; Internal tools</p>
          <h3 class="card__title">Turning three competing sites into one</h3>
          <p class="card__desc">Three siloed teams. Three internal accessibility sites. One consolidation that had been blocked by org politics for years.</p>
        </div>
      </a>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================================
   The Lab
   ============================================================ #}
<section id="lab" class="section section--alt" aria-labelledby="lab-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section__header">
      <h2 class="section__title" id="lab-heading">The Lab</h2>
      <p class="section__intro">Stuff I made for fun, probably at 5am, that nobody asked for.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="lab__grid">
      {% for item in lab %}
        <a class="lab-card" href="{{ item.url }}" {% if item.url != "#" %}rel="external" target="_blank"{% endif %}>
          {% if item.image %}
            <img class="lab-card__image" src="{{ item.image }}" alt="{{ item.image_alt }}">
          {% else %}
            <div class="lab-card__image--placeholder" aria-hidden="true">[ Image ]</div>
          {% endif %}
          <div class="lab-card__body">
            <p class="lab-card__title">{{ item.title }}</p>
            {% if item.description %}
              <p class="lab-card__desc">{{ item.description }}</p>
            {% endif %}
          </div>
        </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================================
   Writing
   ============================================================ #}
<section id="writing" class="section" aria-labelledby="writing-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section__header">
      <h2 class="section__title" id="writing-heading">Writing</h2>
      <p class="section__intro">Design, research, and whatever else I can't stop thinking about.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="writing__list">
      {% for post in collections.writing %}
        <article class="writing-card">
          <p class="writing-card__date">
            <time datetime="{{ post.date | date('yyyy-MM-dd') }}">{{ post.date | date("MMMM d, yyyy") }}</time>
          </p>
          <h3 class="writing-card__title">
            <a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a>
          </h3>
          {% if post.data.description %}
            <p class="writing-card__excerpt">{{ post.data.description }}</p>
          {% endif %}
        </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ============================================================
   About
   ============================================================ #}
<section id="about" class="section section--alt" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section__header">
      <h2 class="section__title" id="about-heading">About</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="about__inner">

      <div class="about__prose">
        <p>I got into UX research because I genuinely cannot stop asking why. Not the polite kind of why — the kind where I need to understand the actual thing behind the thing. I picked up enough code along the way to prototype my own ideas, which means I spend a lot of time at the intersection of "here's what the data says" and "okay but let me just build it real quick and see."</p>

        <p>When I'm not deep in a research synthesis or arguing with Figma, I'm outside. National parks are my reset button — there's something about being in a place that's indifferent to your deadlines that fixes whatever's been stuck. I hike, I run, I do whatever gets me into a forest or up a mountain. The body needs it. The brain needs it more.</p>

        <p>Music is the other thing. I've been playing since I was a kid and making it is the eventual goal — not as a career pivot, just as the thing I'm working toward because it matters to me. I practice more than anyone knows.</p>

        <p>At home there are two cats (Miso and Roux) and a dog (Biscuit) who have very different opinions about personal space and all of them are correct. Every week I make homemade nachos from scratch — actual scratch, not "I opened a bag of chips." It's become a thing. I take it seriously.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="about__photos">
        <figure class="polaroid">
          <img src="{{ '/img/placeholder-photo-1.jpg' | url }}" alt="[ Add a photo of yourself, your pets, or somewhere you've hiked ]">
          <figcaption class="polaroid__caption">[ Caption goes here ]</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="polaroid">
          <img src="{{ '/img/placeholder-photo-2.jpg' | url }}" alt="[ Add a candid photo ]">
          <figcaption class="polaroid__caption">[ Caption goes here ]</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="polaroid">
          <img src="{{ '/img/placeholder-photo-3.jpg' | url }}" alt="[ Add a photo ]">
          <figcaption class="polaroid__caption">[ Caption goes here ]</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="polaroid">
          <img src="{{ '/img/placeholder-photo-4.jpg' | url }}" alt="[ Add a photo ]">
          <figcaption class="polaroid__caption">[ Caption goes here ]</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
